dct_title_s: A new map of Palestine or the Holy Land
dct_description_sm: drawn and engraved by W. H. Gamble.
Coordinates approximate and based on Greenwich meridian.
2 bar scales on map given in "Statute miles" and "Roman miles".
Shows topography, drainage, settlements of the tribes of Israel, roads and travel routes, places of historical interest.
"Entered according to act of Congress in the year 1864, by S. Augustus Mitchell, Jr., in the Clerk's Office of the District Court of the Eastern District of Pensylvania."
Appears in Mitchell's New General Atlas. Philadelphia, S. Augustus Mitchell, Jr., 1864.
